			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">PVC is a popular thermoplastic that's odorless, solid, brittle, and generally white in color. It's used in a variety of applications in the building and construction, health care, electronics, automobile and other sectors. PVC, also known as Polyvinyl chloride, chiefly contains PVC resin and varying proportions of additives. These additives include lubricants, pigments, processing aids, stabilizers, and plasticizers. Ranking third in the most commonly used materials in the world, PVC is quite sturdy and durable.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">PVC 是一种常用的热塑性塑料，无味、坚固、易碎，一般呈白色。它被广泛应用于建筑、保健、电子、汽车和其他领域。PVC 又称聚氯乙烯，主要含有 PVC 树脂和不同比例的添加剂。这些添加剂包括润滑剂、颜料、加工助剂、稳定剂和增塑剂。聚氯乙烯在全球最常用的材料中排名第三，非常坚固耐用。</common:generalComment>
